    {
        "content": "<p>Good point.  Birkoff's HSP variety theorem is intermediate between bog-standard undergrad math and categories; define a lattice closure (which will be familiar from topology) and a variety.  I think it makes a nice transition and motivation for the more abstract categorical picture, actually.</p>",
